President Barack Obama has proclaimed May 2016 as National Physical Fitness and Sports Month in the United States. The proclamation highlights the importance of physical fitness and encourages Americans of all ages to engage in physical activity to maintain their health and well-being. The proclamation emphasizes that regular exercise can relieve stress, boost energy and self-esteem, and prevent chronic diseases. It also emphasizes the importance of healthy eating and proper nutrition, particularly for children, as their well-being tomorrow depends on what they eat today. The proclamation recognizes the efforts of organizations like the President's Council on Fitness, Sports, and Nutrition and the Let's Move! initiative in promoting physical activity and healthy eating. It calls upon the people of the United States to prioritize daily physical activity, sports participation, and good nutrition in their lives.